[1:1] Now the word of Yahweh came to Jonah the son of Amittai, saying,
[1:2] &ldquo;Arise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and preach against it, for their wickedness has come up before me.&rdquo;
[1:3] But Jonah rose up to flee to Tarshish from the presence of Yahweh. He went down to Joppa, and found a ship going to Tarshish; so he paid its fare, and went down into it, to go with them to Tarshish from the presence of Yahweh.

[1:1] And there is a word of Jehovah unto Jonah son of Amittai, saying:
[1:2] `Rise, go unto Nineveh, the great city, and proclaim against it that their wickedness hath come up before Me.&rsquo;
[1:3] And Jonah riseth to flee to Tarshish from the face of Jehovah, and goeth down to' Joppa, and findeth a ship going to&rsquo; Tarshish, and he giveth its fare, and goeth down into it, to go with them to Tarshish from the face of Jehovah.
